# CODEOWNERS — required review for high-trust paths.
#
# This file is the primary defense against a "Pwn Request" — a pull request
# that modifies CI, hooks, or security-relevant config in a way that would
# execute attacker-controlled code on merge. Anything under a rule below
# requires the listed owners to approve before the PR can merge, when combined
# with branch protection's "Require review from Code Owners" setting.
#
# ==============================================================================
# Branch-protection checklist (enable once in repo settings → Branches → main):
#
#   [x] Require a pull request before merging
#   [x] Require approvals (at least 1)
#   [x] Require review from Code Owners
#   [x] Dismiss stale pull request approvals when new commits are pushed
#   [x] Require status checks to pass before merging
#         - ShellCheck
#         - bootstrap.sh --verify
#         - Validate JSON / YAML
#         - Self-scan (gitleaks)
#   [x] Require branches to be up to date before merging
#   [x] Require conversation resolution before merging
#   [x] Do not allow bypassing the above settings (applies to admins too)
# ==============================================================================

# Fallback — everything needs at least one maintainer approval.
*                                   @hallucinationengineer

# CI / GitHub config — the pwn-request primary target.
/.github/                           @hallucinationengineer
/.github/workflows/                 @hallucinationengineer
/.github/CODEOWNERS                 @hallucinationengineer
/.github/dependabot.yml             @hallucinationengineer

# Hook scripts run on every tool call; compromising one bypasses every
# guardrail the baseline provides.
/secure-claude/.claude/hooks/       @hallucinationengineer
/secure-claude/.claude/settings.json @hallucinationengineer

# Installer — anything here runs in the user's shell on install.
/bootstrap.sh                       @hallucinationengineer

# Security policy itself.
/SECURITY.md                        @hallucinationengineer
